<!-- ═══ FOUR PILLARS ═══ -->
<section class="pillars" id="pillars">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="pillars-header">
      <div class="sec-label reveal d1">The Philosophy</div>
      <h2 class="sec-title reveal d1">The Four Pillars</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="pillars-grid">
      <div class="pillar-card reveal d1">
        <div class="pillar-numeral">I</div>
        <div class="pillar-label">Pillar I</div>
        <h3 class="pillar-name">Virtue</h3>
        <div class="pillar-tagline">Do right regardless.</div>
        <div class="pillar-divider"></div>
        <p class="pillar-body">A Grithosian is honest. Not when it is convenient. Not when it is safe. Regardless of the cost. Virtue requires no reward and no recognition. You do right because it is right. That is the only reason a Grithosian needs. Honesty is not a policy. It is a practice — daily, unglamorous, and non-negotiable.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="pillar-card reveal d2">
        <div class="pillar-numeral">II</div>
        <div class="pillar-label">Pillar II</div>
        <h3 class="pillar-name">Apex</h3>
        <div class="pillar-tagline">Own your nature.</div>
        <div class="pillar-divider"></div>
        <p class="pillar-body">Humans are the most capable species on earth. That is not arrogance — it is fact. A Grithosian owns that truth completely and without apology. But apex is not a trophy. It is a weight. With the greatest capability comes the greatest accountability. Shrinking from your potential is not humility. It is a betrayal of your nature.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="pillar-card reveal d3">
        <div class="pillar-numeral">III</div>
        <div class="pillar-label">Pillar III</div>
        <h3 class="pillar-name">Control</h3>
        <div class="pillar-tagline">Live within bounds.</div>
        <div class="pillar-divider"></div>
        <p class="pillar-body">A Grithosian owns four things completely — their thoughts and attitudes, their decisions and actions, their effort and preparation, and their character and integrity. Everything else belongs to the bounds. This is not resignation. A Grithosian redirects. Immediately. Deliberately. God authored the bounds. They are rational. They can be trusted.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="pillar-card reveal d4">
        <div class="pillar-numeral">IV</div>
        <div class="pillar-label">Pillar IV</div>
        <h3 class="pillar-name">Death</h3>
        <div class="pillar-tagline">Return to the whole.</div>
        <div class="pillar-divider"></div>
        <p class="pillar-body">A Grithosian does not fear death. It is not an enemy. It is a conclusion — the natural end of a life fully lived. Your matter rejoins the whole. The universe is permanently and irrevocably different for you having existed in it. Your impact lives on through the people you led and the truth you told when it cost you. Death is not the opposite of life. It is the completion of it.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

